text: Nyctimystes myolae is a tree frog from Papua New Guinea. Scientists found this frog near the village of Myola village, at 2000 meters above sea level. This frog is brown in color. Scientists say it is related to the common big-eyed tree frog, Nyctimystes narinosus. ==References== Category:Frogs of Oceania
title: Nyctimystes myolae
